
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gulkohegde-routing-planes-using-sr-00.pdf'>
    <title>"Separating Routing Planes using Segment Routing", Shraddha Hegde, arkadiy.gulko@thomsonreuters.com</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gulkohegde-routing-planes-using-sr-00.pdf</link>
    <description>Many network deployments arrange the network topologies in two or more planes.  The traffic generally uses one of the planes and fails over to the other plane when there are link or node failure.  Certain applications require the traffic to be strictly restricted to a particular plane and should not failover to the other plane.  This document proposes a solution for the strict planar routing using Segment Routing.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-03-13T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
